Date: Wed 25 Oct 2017
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2017; 30(43) [edited] http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=25105


Newcastle disease [NCD], Bulgaria
---------------------------------
Information received on 25 Oct 2017 from Dr Damyan Iliev, Chief Veterinary Officer and Deputy Executive Director, Bulgarian Food Safety Agency, Ministry of Agriculture and Food, Sofia, Bulgaria

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 25 Oct 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 25 Oct 2017
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 13 Oct 2017
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Newcastle disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory basic
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Fotinovo, Kardzali
Date of start of the outbreak: 25 Oct 2017
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: backyard
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Birds / 348 / 207 / 207 / 141 / 0

Outbreak statistics: [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 59.48 / 59.48 / 100 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak (s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures: movement control inside the country, vaccination in response to the outbreak (s), surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, screening, traceability, quarantine, official destruction of animal products, official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste, stamping out, zoning, disinfection, no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National reference laboratory for Avian Influenza and Newcastle Disease (national laboratory) / Birds / real-time PCR / 25 Oct 2017 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

